{"type":"message","id":"ae1af68a","parentId":"4f30f25d","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:03:29.000Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issues:\n\n1. **Orphan transcripts**: 98 orphan transcript files in sessions - not critical but worth cleaning up\n2. **Session lock**: There's a lock file from pid=2912 that's alive and 50s old\n3. **Gateway service config issue**: The service command doesn't include the gateway subcommand\n4. **Plugin warning**: openclaw-lark loaded without install/load-path provenance - recommended to set plugins.allow\n\nThe key problem for the gateway restart issue seems to be the \"Gateway service config\" issue - \"Service command does not include the gateway subcommand\". This likely means the scheduled task for the gateway service isn't configured correctly, causing it to fail to restart.\n\n\nThe restart failures with \"Gateway closed (1000)\" happened because the service command is missing the gateway subcommand, so it wasn't properly restarting. I should run the fix command to resolve this.","thinkingSignature":"7aec2e585e740761ad96ec03097ec7b689f1132e26b09a271c0b74cea0077be3"},{"type":"text","text":"\n找到问题了。医生报告里有两个和网关重启失败直接相关的警告：\n\n1. **\"Service command does not include the gateway subcommand\"** — 计划任务启动网关时命令不完整，所以反复启动失败\n2. **Session lock 文件存在** — pid=2912 的进程还活着但可能卡住了\n\n要我帮你运行 `openclaw doctor --fix` 修复这些问题吗？另外建议同时设置 `plugins.allow` 把 `openclaw-lark` 加入白名单，消除那个安全警告。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7293,"output":293,"cacheRead":38726,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46312,"cost":{"input":0.0029172000000000004,"output":0.0004395,"cacheRead":0.00154904,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0049057400000000004}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773921793358}}
{"type":"message","id":"52930667","parentId":"ae1af68a","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:04:53.996Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-19 20:04 GMT+8] PS C:\\Users\\Administrator> powershell.exe -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File \"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\scripts\\gateway-watchdog.ps1\"\n2026/03/19 19:56:50 [INFO] === Watchdog Started (Manual) ===\n2026/03/19 19:56:50 [INFO] Gateway running (startup: Manual)\n2026/03/19 19:57:53 [WARN] Gateway down, restart attempt #1\n2026/03/19 19:57:58 [INFO] Starting Gateway (Watchdog)\n2026/03/19 19:58:05 [ERROR] Gateway start failed\n2026/03/19 19:58:37 [WARN] Gateway down, restart attempt #2\n2026/03/19 19:58:42 [INFO] Starting Gateway (Watchdog)\n2026/03/19 19:58:49 [ERROR] Gateway start failed\n2026/03/19 19:59:21 [WARN] Gateway down, restart attempt #3\n2026/03/19 19:59:26 [INFO] Starting Gateway (Watchdog)\n2026/03/19 19:59:33 [ERROR] Gateway start failed"}],"timestamp":1773921893994}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2afc972","parentId":"52930667","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:05:00.638Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is showing me the gateway watchdog log. The watchdog is trying to restart the gateway but it keeps failing. Let me look at the watchdog script to understand what command it's running, and also check the gateway logs more carefully.\n\nThe watchdog is showing \"Gateway start failed\" but not the actual error. Let me check the watchdog script and the OpenClaw logs to find the actual error message.","thinkingSignature":"941c7030e5a69401f9d53d53faaa936555c22640ff21d1f41cfacdac754f0222"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pgx86tr48rp5_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\scripts\\gateway-watchdog.ps1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pgx86tr48rp5_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw logs --lines 200 2>&1 | Select-Object -Last 100","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":159,"output":167,"cacheRead":41244,"cacheWrite":4637,"totalTokens":46207,"cost":{"input":0.0000636,"output":0.0002505,"cacheRead":0.0016497600000000001,"cacheWrite":0.00069555,"total":0.00265941}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773921893996}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b082e88","parentId":"d2afc972","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:05:00.753Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pgx86tr48rp5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"$GatewayPort = 18789\n$CheckInterval = 30\n$LogDir = \"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\logs\"\n$LogFile = \"$LogDir\\gateway-startup.log\"\n\nif (-not (Test-Path $LogDir)) {\n    New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $LogDir -Force | Out-Null\n}\n\nfunction Write-Log {\n    param([string]$Type, [string]$Message)\n    $Timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy/MM/dd HH:mm:ss\"\n    Add-Content -Path $LogFile -Value \"$Timestamp [$Type] $Message\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    Write-Host \"$Timestamp [$Type] $Message\"\n}\n\nfunction Test-Gateway {\n    try {\n        $client = New-Object System.Net.Sockets.TcpClient\n        $client.Connect(\"127.0.0.1\", $GatewayPort)\n        $client.Close()\n        return $true\n    } catch {\n        return $false\n    }\n}\n\n$StartupType = if ($env:OPENCLAW_WATCHDOG -eq \"1\") { \"Watchdog\" } else { \"Manual\" }\nWrite-Log \"INFO\" \"=== Watchdog Started ($StartupType) ===\"\n\nif (Test-Gateway) {\n    Write-Log \"INFO\" \"Gateway running (startup: $StartupType)\"\n}\n\n$count = 0\nwhile ($true) {\n    if (-not (Test-Gateway)) {\n        $count++\n        Write-Log \"WARN\" \"Gateway down, restart attempt #$count\"\n        Stop-Process -Name \"node\" -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n        Start-Sleep -Seconds 3\n        for ($i = 0; $i -lt 10; $i++) {\n            try {\n                $c = New-Object System.Net.Sockets.TcpClient\n                $c.Connect(\"127.0.0.1\", $GatewayPort)\n                $c.Close()\n                Start-Sleep -Seconds 2\n            } catch { break }\n        }\n        Write-Log \"INFO\" \"Starting Gateway (Watchdog)\"\n        Start-Process -FilePath \"openclaw\" -ArgumentList \"gateway\",\"start\" -WindowStyle Hidden -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n        Start-Sleep -Seconds 5\n        if (Test-Gateway) {\n            Write-Log \"INFO\" \"Gateway started OK\"\n            $count = 0\n        } else {\n            Write-Log \"ERROR\" \"Gateway start failed\"\n        }\n    }\n    Start-Sleep -Seconds $CheckInterval\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773921900702}}
