{"type":"message","id":"0641bef2","parentId":"4698291d","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:15:40.146Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user ran `openclaw gateway` (without a subcommand) which just printed the banner and plugin info and exited - that's the expected behavior when running `openclaw gateway` without `start`, `stop`, `restart`, etc. It showed the banner and loaded plugins, then exited because no subcommand was provided.\n\nThis is different from `openclaw gateway start` which actually starts the gateway as a background service.\n\nThe gateway was already running (from the previous restart via the tool), which is why the status showed it as ok. The user's `openclaw gateway` command without a subcommand just showed the banner and didn't affect the running gateway.\n\nSo the situation is: the gateway is running fine. \n\nThe user might be getting confused about what `openclaw gateway` does versus the subcommands - they're seeing the banner output and thinking something's wrong, but the gateway is actually still running fine from the earlier restart.","thinkingSignature":"334d8c3150e38a37e5e7156efcb30e88eef971193d920eeccd76c19033b7926e"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\n没事儿的——`openclaw gateway` 不带子命令只会打印版本信息和插件列表，然后直接退出，不会影响正在跑的服务。网关一直在正常运行中（刚才 status 显示 RPC probe: ok）。\n\n之前让你觉得\"又不行了\"的，应该是 watchdog 脚本在后台反复重启的那个时段。现在网关是稳的，你不用管它了。\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":159,"output":265,"cacheRead":59157,"cacheWrite":1191,"totalTokens":60772,"cost":{"input":0.0000636,"output":0.0003975,"cacheRead":0.00236628,"cacheWrite":0.00017864999999999998,"total":0.00300603}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773922529558}}
