{"type":"message","id":"608a2002","parentId":"0158bdc9","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:21:59.036Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway is running (RPC probe: ok, Listening: 127.0.0.1:18789). The service command still shows the old/wrong command, but the gateway is running. The issue is that the gateway start command doesn't register as a \"service\" in the way the Scheduled Task shows - it starts a process that keeps running.\n\nThe key diagnostic info: \"RPC probe: ok\" and \"Listening: 127.0.0.1:18789\" - the gateway IS running. The warnings about the service command are about the Scheduled Task configuration, but the actual gateway process is running fine.\n\nNow the problem is the Scheduled Task service configuration is out of date - but since the task is disabled anyway, it doesn't matter for now.\n\n\nThe real question is whether the gateway will survive a system reboot or if I need to fix the Scheduled Task. Since the task is currently disabled and the gateway is running fine through a manual process, I should let the user know everything is working and check if they want to reboot to test persistence.","thinkingSignature":"9544b64a36aaf6bfefe184f5f14f852d2fd43bb3ddba789f9d73ecfe4c0c3827"},{"type":"text","text":"网关在跑（RPC probe: ok，端口 18789 监听中）。计划任务那个警告还在，但不影响当前运行——问题是任务被禁用了，而且即便启用它也用的是旧命令。\n\n现在你那边能正常和我对话了吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":28222,"output":268,"cacheRead":38726,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67216,"cost":{"input":0.011288800000000002,"output":0.000402,"cacheRead":0.00154904,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.013239840000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773922909550}}
