{"type":"message","id":"93605e7a","parentId":"35ad61c9","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:22:29.733Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why `openclaw gateway start` didn't seem to do anything. Looking at the output from earlier, when they ran `openclaw gateway start`, it just returned to the prompt with no output. This is because `openclaw gateway start` manages the **Windows Scheduled Task** service, not the actual process. Since the Scheduled Task was disabled, `start` just enabled it (or tried to) but it doesn't actually run the gateway in the foreground.\n\nThe `openclaw gateway start` command manages the **service** (Scheduled Task on Windows), it doesn't run the gateway directly. So when they ran `openclaw gateway start`, it probably just enabled the scheduled task but since the task was already in a weird state, nothing visible happened.\n \nThe distinction is that `openclaw gateway run` actually starts the gateway directly in the foreground, whereas `start` and `stop` only manage the scheduled task service. The real issue is that the gateway process itself is already running from some prior invocation, which is why the port is already listening.","thinkingSignature":"3b41d0044cbcfda90a5116595d349aff119f00d54a91bdba72cfbeff6e2c09f4"},{"type":"text","text":"因为 `openclaw gateway start` 操控的是 **Windows 计划任务服务**，不是直接跑进程。它只是告诉 Windows \"启动那个任务\"，任务内容是执行 `gateway.cmd`——而 `gateway.cmd` 里虽然有正确的启动命令，但任务本身是 **disabled** 状态，所以 start 相当于什么都没做。\n\n真正在前台跑网关用的是 `openclaw gateway run`，但一般不需要——有个 node 进程已经在监听 18789 了，说明之前某次手动 `gateway run` 残留下来的。\n\n你要我把那个旧的计划任务删掉，然后重新注册一个正确的吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":159,"output":338,"cacheRead":65984,"cacheWrite":878,"totalTokens":67359,"cost":{"input":0.0000636,"output":0.000507,"cacheRead":0.00263936,"cacheWrite":0.0001317,"total":0.0033416599999999998}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773922940160}}
