{"type":"message","id":"47076db7","parentId":"7ae77303","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:24:25.268Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sir is asking why when I restarted, it opened the openclaw.ps1 file again. This is likely because the gateway restart command (`openclaw gateway restart`) internally uses the Windows scheduled task mechanism, which runs `gateway.cmd`, and that in turn runs `openclaw` commands. But actually the issue might be different - when the gateway restarts via the RPC call, it might be invoking the openclaw.ps1 script.\n\nWait, actually when I ran `openclaw gateway restart`, the `exec` tool ran the command `openclaw gateway restart 2>&1`. The `openclaw` is a PowerShell script (`openclaw.ps1`). So when the exec tool runs this command, it's running `C:\\Users\\Administrator\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\openclaw.ps1 gateway restart`. This is just how the command is executed - it's not opening any file directly.\n \nBut if Sir is seeing the `opendaw.ps1` file open in an editor, that might be something else - perhaps a side effect of the restart process or a separate action that got triggered. Looking back at what happened, I ran `openclaw gateway uninstall` which probably triggered a gateway shutdown, and then the restart behavior might have opened something unexpected.\n\nActually, when I called `gateway restart`, it shut down the gateway process which caused this webchat session to disconnect temporarily. The status showed the gateway wasn't responding, but it recovered on its own. That reset might have triggered some behavior that opened the `opendaw.ps1` file - either the watchdog script or something in the restart sequence itself. I think the real issue is that when the gateway service stops and restarts, it terminates the node process that was handling the exec call, which could explain why a window appeared or something got interrupted on Sir's end.","thinkingSignature":"3b632d0d0be3a76075409a54572b44aa028742941bc4b016d26b2c0bcb4338a4"},{"type":"text","text":"我没有主动打开任何文件——`openclaw gateway restart` 是通过 RPC 告诉网关进程自己重启的。网关关闭时所有现有连接会断开，你看到的内容可能是：\n\n1. 网关重启时当前 session 断开了，控制权临时交回给 launcher\n2. launcher（就是 `opendaw.ps1`）检测到网关不在，就自动又把它拉起来了\n\n你说的\"打开了 opendaw.ps1\"是指 PowerShell 窗口里显示了脚本内容，还是文件在编辑器里被打开了？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":133,"output":478,"cacheRead":67205,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67816,"cost":{"input":0.000053200000000000006,"output":0.000717,"cacheRead":0.0026882,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0034584}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773923049318}}
