{"type":"message","id":"4038b91e","parentId":"32067b4c","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:25:22.936Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying that the opendaw.ps1 file was opened in a text editor. This is likely because when the gateway restarts, some process (possibly the launcher/batch script) is reopening the file in the default editor on Windows. This could be related to how the gateway.cmd or some other script is being invoked.\n\nActually, thinking about it more carefully - when the gateway crashes or restarts, the command prompt window that was running the gateway might show the script that was running. But the user says it was opened in a \"text editor.\"\n\nOn Windows, `.ps1` files are associated with PowerShell ISE or VS Code or Notepad. If some process is calling the script without `-ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File` properly, Windows might open the file in the default editor instead of executing it.\n \nSo the sequence is probably that when `openclaw gateway start` runs, it attempts to launch the scheduled task, which then tries to execute `gateway.cmd`. If that fails because the task is disabled, something else triggers the `.ps1` file to open in the editor instead of executing it - possibly Windows file association behavior or how the script is being invoked.","thinkingSignature":"52f25f1889cec9d30d48b93a85626558e586424198850d35a7a7784e7eec13bc"},{"type":"text","text":"那个很可能是 `openclaw gateway start` 触发计划任务时，Windows 对 `.ps1` 文件的默认处理行为——某些情况下文件没有被\"执行\"而是被\"打开\"了。\n\n我先帮你把旧任务删掉，然后重新注册一个正确的：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8rj6g3o6hiz0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"schtasks /Delete /TN \"OpenClaw Gateway\" /F 2>&1; echo \"Exit: $LASTEXITCODE\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":159,"output":358,"cacheRead":67168,"cacheWrite":180,"totalTokens":67865,"cost":{"input":0.0000636,"output":0.000537,"cacheRead":0.00268672,"cacheWrit