{"type":"message","id":"65f18753","parentId":"cf4b9835","timestamp":"2026-03-19T12:25:44.825Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The new scheduled task still just runs `gateway.cmd`. The key is whether `gateway.cmd` itself has the correct command. And from our earlier reading of `gateway.cmd`, it does have the correct full command:\n\n```\n\"C:\\Program Files\\nodejs\\node.exe\" C:\\Users\\Administrator\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\dist\\index.js gateway --port 18789\n```\n\nSo the task runs `gateway.cmd`, which then runs the correct node command with `gateway` subcommand. So the \"Service command does not include the gateway subcommand\" warning from `openclaw doctor` is actually misleading - it checks the scheduled task's `Command` (which is `gateway.cmd`), not the actual content of the batch script.","thinkingSignature":"501dcfa395c2dc2d992cc040e178f51659af223d6e42b35a6f98e1952eb9d040"},{"type":"text","text":"计划任务现在正确了——它执行 `gateway.cmd`，而 `gateway.cmd` 里的实际命令是带 `gateway` 子命令的：\n\n```\nnode.exe ...\\openclaw\\dist\\index.js gateway --port 18789\n```\n\n所以这次 `openclaw gateway start` 应该能正常启动服务了。你现在可以关掉后台那些乱七八糟的进程，然后试试 `openclaw gateway start` 看能不能起来。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29756,"output":242,"cacheRead":38726,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68724,"cost":{"input":0.0119024,"output":0.000363,"cacheRead":0.00154904,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01381444}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773923137295}}
