{"type":"message","id":"d51a4f90","parentId":"47e74fbb","timestamp":"2026-03-19T13:47:05.082Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying there's no \"message receiving mode\" option in the Feishu open platform settings for their bot. They might be referring to a specific bot's configuration. Let me think about this - in Feishu's open platform, for bot messages in groups, there's typically a setting about whether the bot can be mentioned (@) or can receive all messages.\n\nActually, in Feishu's bot configuration, there are two modes:\n1. \"订阅模式\" (subscription mode) - only receives messages when @mentioned\n2. \"对话模式\" (conversation mode) - can receive all messages in the group\n\nThe user is saying they can't find a \"message receiving mode\" setting. \n\nOn Feishu, bots generally need to be @mentioned in groups to receive messages - there's no built-in mode to receive all messages without being mentioned. But there's a webhook capability that could work around this limitation. I should clarify what the user is trying to achieve with their bot configuration.","thinkingSignature":"12d7fb8b416b562cdcd304f1cfeff0d1dac5c0136be9ee2ff991920892dc628f"},{"type":"text","text":"飞书群里机器人**默认都需要 @ 才能收到消息**，没有\"接收所有消息\"的开关。\n\n有两个思路可以绕过：\n\n1. **用飞书 Webhook 机器人** — 在群里加一个\"Incoming Webhook\"类型的机器人，它不受 @ 限制，可以直接往群里发消息，但只能发送不能接收。\n\n2. **用工作流机器人** — 配置一个飞书自建应用，通过 API 直接把消息推送到群里指定会话，绕过人 @ 机器人的限制。\n\nSir 的需求是：**机器人不用被 @ 就能往群里发消息**，还是**机器人不用被 @ 就能听到群里所有消息**？前者可以解决，后者飞书本身不支持。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":147,"output":343,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":74494,"totalTokens":74984,"cost":{"input":0.000058800000000000006,"output":0.0005145,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.0111741,"total":0.0117474}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773928006994}}
{"type":"message","id":"d4640af0","parentId":"d51a4f90","timestamp":"2026-03-19T13:54:29.413Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-19 21:54:28 GMT+8] Feishu[main] DM | ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389 [msg:om_x100b54f44ff884b0c29cb19a0bb0ae8]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54f44ff884b0c29cb19a0bb0ae8\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-19 21:54 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389\"\n}\n```\n\n要听啊"}],"timestamp":1773928469410}}
{"type":"message","id":"79cab051","parentId":"d4640af0","timestamp":"2026-03-19T13:54:48.040Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants the bot to listen to all messages in a Feishu group without being @mentioned. This is a fundamental limitation of Feishu's bot platform - bots can only receive messages when they are @mentioned in groups. There's no setting to change this.\n\nHowever, there might be a workaround using the Feishu API directly. Let me think...\n\nActually, looking at the Feishu API documentation, there are a few approaches:\n1. The bot can use the \"receive_v2\" endpoint with message_events subscription\n2. But even with that, Feishu group bots still require @mention for regular messages\n\nThe only way to truly \"listen\" to all messages without being @mentioned would be:\n\n\n1. Using the Feishu \"Events\" platform - subscribe to `im.message.receive_v1` events\n2. But this still only fires when the bot is @mentioned in groups\n\nThe real issue is that Feishu fundamentally requires bots to be @mentioned in group chats to receive messages. Even with the Events API subscription, this limitation persists. The alternative would be using a \"Custom Bot\" with Webhook, but that only allows sending messages, not receiving them.\n\nFor proactive group monitoring without @mention, I'd need either a user token with message read permissions to pull messages via API, or to leverage the Feishu Lark Next Bot which might handle this differently. But honestly, this is a platform constraint with no clean workaround through OpenClaw's configuration.","thinkingSignature":"128cef8e0765547974d7b156691df492c83acebb9d6d4d5c49445c0ae9ce487e"},{"type":"text","text":"这是**飞书平台本身的限制**，群里的普通机器人必须被 @ 才能收消息，没有开关可以改。\n\n不过有一个偏方：飞书支持通过 **API 主动拉取群消息**，不依赖 @ 触发——可以用一个定时任务（比如 cron）每分钟调一次 `im/v1/messages`，把群里最近的消息同步过来，绕过\"必须被 @ 才能收\"这个限制。\n\n但这需要：1) 拿到群里消息的 API 权限；2) 写个定时脚本持续轮询。\n\nSir 想用这种方式让某个 agent 监听特定群的消息吗？告诉我你想监听哪个群和用来做什么。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":147,"output":443,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":74917,"totalTokens":75507,"cost":{"input":0.000058800000000000006,"output":0.0006645,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.011237549999999999,"total":0.011960849999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773928469412}}
{"type":"message","id":"93aa4524","parentId":"79cab051","timestamp":"2026-03-19T13:57:04.203Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-19 21:57:03 GMT+8] Feishu[main] DM | ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389 [msg:om_x100b54f4441294a0b26c70af2629a3d]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b54f4441294a0b26c70af2629a3d\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-19 21:57 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_c0acf4e14a9895533f121340f36ca389\"\n}\n```\n\n给每个agent配置agent to agent"}],"timestamp":1773928624200}}
{"type":"message","id":"257e3814","parentId":"93aa4524","timestamp":"2026-03-19T13:57:17.935Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to configure agent-to-agent communication. This means each agent should be able to send messages to other agents. Looking at the context, we have 5 agents: main, coder, newsai, pm, finance. The user wants them to be able to talk to each other.\n\nThis is an OpenClaw configuration feature. In OpenClaw, agents can communicate with each other through the sessions system. The `sessions_send` tool allows sending messages between agents.\n\nHowever, for agents to communicate autonomously (without me manually forwarding), we'd need to configure something like agent-to-agent messaging capabilities. \n\nLooking at the OpenClaw docs, I think the user might be referring to OpenClaw's multi-agent communication features. Let me think about what's actually possible here.\n\nIn OpenClaw's architecture, each agent is a separate session store. They can send messages to each other via `sessions_send`. But for agents to proactively send messages to each other, we'd need:\n\n\n1. Each agent to have a way to know when to trigger\n2. Some kind of agent-to-agent protocol or configuration\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the user might be talking about configuring agents to communicate with each other through Feishu, or through OpenClaw's internal messaging system. Or they might want each agent to be able to send messages to the user's other agents.\n\nWait, re-reading the request: \"给每个agent配置agent to agent\" - configure agent to agent communication for each agent. This probably means they want each agent to be able to initiate communication with other agents, not just receive messages. This is a reasonable feature request in OpenClaw's multi-agent system.\n\nI should check the OpenClaw configuration to see what agent-to-agent settings are actually available.","thinkingSignature":"f96ebee41acb5c6b923bff6cf6a748d7c5241ceaed9efbac77f1ced3e65fe02d"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_754ko03leuhn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config get agents 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":147,"output":403,"cacheRead":74842,"cacheWrite":495,"totalTokens":75887,"cost":{"input":0.000058800000000000006,"output":0.0006045,"cacheRead":0.00299368,"cacheWrite":0.00007425,"total":0.00373123}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773928624202}}
