{"type":"message","id":"b0c16e3f","parentId":"9fa690b2","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:15:45.750Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The subagent token budget is not a configurable item through `openclaw config`. Let me look at the OpenClaw docs to see how to configure subagent budgets.\n\nActually, looking at the `sessions_spawn` tool parameters, there's no `maxTokens` parameter. The token budget is controlled by the model itself and the runtime limits. \n\nActually, the session-level `runTimeoutSeconds` parameter controls the timeout, not token budget. And looking at the subagent announce result, it showed \"tokens 230.3k\" for a session that ran for 2 minutes. So it seems the subagent might have a hard token limit based on the model context window and the billing/policy limits.\n\n\nThe real bottleneck might not be token limits at all—the news fetch and Feishu message send are both network operations, and when newsai is spawned as a subagent of main, it's the main agent's context being reused, which could be compounding the inefficiency. I should look at the OpenClaw documentation to see if there are any configurable timeout or budget settings for spawned subagents.","thinkingSignature":"d98072ff40f8d2cb8a48eea38dbc3b01a2c27866731b3375d4dfa5b02a67c5e9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p4gyz1eaei5x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49368,"output":291,"cacheRead":36971,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":86630,"cost":{"input":0.019747200000000003,"output":0.0004365,"cacheRead":0.00147884,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02166254}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773929736257}}
