{"type":"message","id":"0dde884a","parentId":"318be0e7","timestamp":"2026-03-19T14:35:16.623Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The OAuth authorization has been revoked. Now the system should automatically re-initiate the OAuth flow when the next tool call is made. But since the user is on Feishu, and the system is configured with feishu, the re-authorization should happen automatically.\n\nActually, wait - I need to think about this. The user just revoked OAuth. Now the next time a feishu tool that needs user authorization is called, it should automatically prompt for re-authorization. But since I'm in a conversation with the user on Feishu, the system should be able to guide the user through the OAuth flow.\n\nActually, I'm not sure if the system will automatically re-initiate the OAuth flow or if the user needs to do something. \n\nThe system documentation says it automatically re-authorizes after revocation, but I think what actually happens is the next time a tool requiring that authorization is called, the system will detect the revoked token and prompt the user to re-authorize through whatever channel is configured—in this case, Feishu. Since I just revoked the OAuth, I should try calling a tool that requires it to see if the re-authorization flow triggers automatically.","thinkingSignature":"7ec51335a150e195fa8bda628b200a5aaa687fbb4fdbdc3138b77c8823ab5336"},{"type":"text","text":"已撤销 Sir 的飞书授权。下次调用需要用户身份的工具时，系统会自动重新发起授权流程。\n\n现在我试试用 Sir 的身份发一条消息，看能不能触发重新授权："}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":61225,"output":277,"cacheRead":36971,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":98473,"cost":{"input":0.02449,"output":0.0004155,"cacheRead":0.00147884,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02638434}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773930906445}}
