{"type":"message","id":"ce2b8cc1","parentId":"f0031fda","timestamp":"2026-03-19T15:00:09.488Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No cryptography module. Let me try with ssh-keygen using Start-Process with proper stdin handling. Or I can generate an RSA key pair which is more widely supported.Let me try a different approach - use the `-p` (passphrase) option to provide an empty passphrase via stdin, or use `-q` (quiet) mode.\n\nActually the issue is that ssh-keygen prompts for a passphrase interactively. In PowerShell without a TTY, this doesn't work well. Let me try using `echo \"\" | ssh-keygen` or using `-P \"\"` to provide empty passphrase. \n\nActually ssh-keygen on Windows when called from non-interactive shell might not work well. \n\nLet me check if there's already an SSH key present or if `ssh-keygen -A` could help generate the host keys automatically.","thinkingSignature":"dbcef03aa69418ed783059ba2b0a2d4c76666bd0dfb9a8d33b5ff2d38047632c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0s8ylbfu3ii5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -f \"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.ssh\\id_ed25519\" -C \"openclaw-backup\" -q -P \"\" 2>&1; echo \"Exit: $LASTEXITCODE\"; Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.ssh\\id_ed25519.pub\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":88481,"output":276,"cacheRead":36971,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":125728,"cost":{"input":0.035392400000000004,"output":0.00041400000000000003,"cacheRead":0.00147884,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.037285240000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773932400976}}
